WEBVTT

00:02.461 --> 00:06.454
Dragon:
In a land of myth and a time of magic...

00:06.632 --> 00:08.122
The destiny of a great kingdom...

00:08.300 --> 00:10.837
Rests on the shoulders
of a young man.

00:11.261 --> 00:14.503
His name: Merlin.

00:17.142 --> 00:20.350
The prophets speak of Arthur's bane.

00:20.938 --> 00:22.929
You would do well to fear it.

00:23.106 --> 00:26.690
For it stalks him
like a ghost in the night.

00:29.696 --> 00:31.549
Ruadan: Arthur's bane is
real once it is known to us.

00:31.573 --> 00:33.655
- His end is nigh.
- So you keep saying.

00:33.867 --> 00:36.734
- Yet you cannot tell me what it is.
- The diamair will tell us.

00:36.912 --> 00:38.743
The diamair is the key
to all knowledge.

00:39.289 --> 00:40.529
Then where is this key?

00:42.042 --> 00:43.828
It is here beneath your feet.

00:44.545 --> 00:45.955
There's something out there.

00:46.505 --> 00:48.786
- Did you see that?
- I'm not sure we should go to ismere.

00:49.091 --> 00:51.207
Arthur:
I swear I'm going to rescue my men...

00:51.385 --> 00:52.545
Or die trying.

00:56.223 --> 00:57.633
Merlin!

01:01.353 --> 01:03.093
- Not so fast.
- Stop!

01:03.438 --> 01:06.475
Shouldn't we leave it to the lady morgana
to decide their fate?

01:06.984 --> 01:08.849
- Mordred.
- Hello, Arthur.

02:21.433 --> 02:22.639
Aithusa?

02:28.982 --> 02:30.222
Come.

02:31.485 --> 02:32.850
Come here.

02:36.114 --> 02:37.695
Don't worry.

02:39.201 --> 02:40.566
We're safe.

02:42.204 --> 02:43.819
No harm can come to us now.

02:46.375 --> 02:48.661
Our troubles are
all in the past.

02:50.629 --> 02:52.369
I promise.

03:00.764 --> 03:02.470
Soon we will have the diamair.

03:04.017 --> 03:06.349
Soon we will know Arthur's bane.

03:07.896 --> 03:09.932
Camelot will be ours.

03:18.949 --> 03:20.234
Arthur: Remind me, Merlin...

03:20.409 --> 03:22.070
How did we end up like this?

03:22.869 --> 03:26.453
Oh, yes, you were thinking
about your stomach as usual.

03:26.665 --> 03:28.075
I told you it was a trap.

03:30.127 --> 03:31.833
Merlin! Man: Hold!

03:37.217 --> 03:40.960
We can't let them hand us over to morgana.
We need to get out of here. We need a plan.

03:41.346 --> 03:44.304
You speak when you're spoken to.

03:45.892 --> 03:47.507
Faster.

04:07.330 --> 04:08.661
Here

04:09.666 --> 04:10.746
- drink this.
- No.

04:10.917 --> 04:14.501
- It will make it easier to bear.
- No, Gaius, you have to help me.

04:14.880 --> 04:16.336
Please, speak to the queen.

04:16.505 --> 04:18.212
- It will do no good.
- Then let me.

04:19.634 --> 04:22.467
Please, it's all I ask.
Allow me to meet with her.

04:22.637 --> 04:25.253
- I'm just a physician.
- But she listens to you.

04:25.432 --> 04:28.549
She trusts you.
Please, all I want is to talk with her.

04:29.269 --> 04:31.134
If you don't help me, Gaius...

04:31.938 --> 04:33.144
Please don't let me die.

04:33.482 --> 04:34.642
Please.

04:54.795 --> 04:56.251
What are you gawping at?

05:02.427 --> 05:04.008
Is this what you want?

05:08.183 --> 05:09.423
Catch.

05:13.605 --> 05:14.965
Mordred:
Maybe we should feed them.

05:15.106 --> 05:16.346
What for?

05:16.566 --> 05:19.433
- They'll be skin and bones.
- Morgana wants slaves...

05:19.694 --> 05:21.480
Not hogs for the fire.

05:22.531 --> 05:23.611
Then slow the pace.

05:24.574 --> 05:26.530
The quicker we get there...

05:26.785 --> 05:28.070
The quicker I get my money.

06:40.108 --> 06:42.690
- Do you want them?
- Why are you doing this?

06:44.946 --> 06:46.277
He once saved my life.

06:46.865 --> 06:48.480
I owe him a debt.

06:49.367 --> 06:50.982
Don't be so quick to judge me.

06:56.249 --> 06:58.615
You fear me, emrys. Don't you?

07:00.420 --> 07:04.629
I know the hatred and suspicion
with which men treat those with magic.

07:05.383 --> 07:08.591
You and I are not so different.

07:09.679 --> 07:12.421
L, too, have learned to hide my gifts.

07:17.938 --> 07:21.556
I promise your secret
is safe with me.

07:24.986 --> 07:27.352
What's morgana looking for in ismere”?

07:31.409 --> 07:32.409
The diamair.

07:33.078 --> 07:34.659
What's that?

07:35.163 --> 07:37.495
In the language of my people,
it means "the key."

07:38.041 --> 07:39.247
The key to what?

07:40.502 --> 07:42.367
The key to all knowledge.

07:58.436 --> 08:00.392
There is still no sign of the diamar.

08:01.022 --> 08:02.228
We're running out of time!

08:02.732 --> 08:04.268
Have faith, morgana.

08:04.442 --> 08:06.023
Arthur could be on us in days.

08:06.194 --> 08:09.482
- Or he could be dead.
- No, he escaped. I'm sure of it.

08:09.864 --> 08:11.320
He'll be in Camelot by now.

08:11.491 --> 08:14.491
