18:15.886 --> 18:17.126
Stop.

18:24.437 --> 18:26.098
Reveal yourself.

19:07.313 --> 19:08.473
Come on.

19:26.540 --> 19:28.576
- Is it ruadan?
- Leon: Most certainly.

19:44.517 --> 19:45.597
There!

19:50.773 --> 19:52.229
Give yourselves up.

19:53.317 --> 19:54.557
There's no escape.

20:22.847 --> 20:24.053
Father!

21:04.764 --> 21:06.004
I need water.

21:24.366 --> 21:26.573
- Father.
- The fight must continue.

21:26.744 --> 21:29.110
- You must cure yourself.
- I do not have such powers.

21:29.288 --> 21:30.869
Try, please.

21:44.261 --> 21:46.092
Attach this to the bird.

22:08.536 --> 22:09.867
You've done very well.

22:11.205 --> 22:13.070
You should be proud.

22:18.254 --> 22:19.744
Sefa.

22:20.965 --> 22:22.921
- You can't leave me.
- You must be strong.

22:23.092 --> 22:24.502
Feather, please.

22:27.263 --> 22:29.219
I will always love you.

23:22.693 --> 23:24.479
Ruadan: I bring bad tidings.

23:24.820 --> 23:26.902
Arthur did not return to Camelot.

23:27.114 --> 23:28.979
He makes his way to ismere.

23:29.325 --> 23:31.611
But you must not despair, morgana.

23:31.952 --> 23:33.442
Soon you will have the diamair...

23:33.621 --> 23:36.283
And Arthur's bane will be in your grasp.

23:36.582 --> 23:39.574
Soon the pendragons will be no more.

23:43.881 --> 23:46.167
Arthur:
You know what they say, Merlin:

23:46.800 --> 23:48.961
Appearances can be deceiving.

23:49.887 --> 23:52.048
Not in this case.

24:08.489 --> 24:10.150
Gwen: What is it?

24:12.826 --> 24:15.408
I believe it's a prayer.

24:27.007 --> 24:28.338
Gwen: Can you read it?

24:30.719 --> 24:31.719
(Gaius?

24:31.887 --> 24:34.879
I'm no expert in the druidic runes.

24:35.057 --> 24:38.015
Please. I know you too well.

24:39.520 --> 24:42.432
It's a call for victory over the enemies
of the old religion.

24:44.274 --> 24:46.310
I thought the druids
were a peaceful people.

24:46.568 --> 24:47.808
For the most part, they are.

24:47.987 --> 24:50.103
But for some,
the great purge changed that.

24:50.280 --> 24:52.362
They blame uther for their suffering.

24:52.741 --> 24:54.106
But he's long been dead.

24:54.284 --> 24:57.151
Some believe that Arthur
is no different from his father.

24:57.371 --> 24:58.986
Sorcery is still outlawed.

24:59.206 --> 25:01.868
For them, little has changed.

25:02.876 --> 25:05.993
So ruadan believed it was his
sacred duty to fight my husband.

25:06.171 --> 25:08.662
More than that,
there are those who believe

25:08.882 --> 25:12.124
that Arthur is destined
to die by a druid's hand.

25:13.762 --> 25:16.219
Perhaps ruadan thought
he was that man.

25:16.724 --> 25:18.885
Well, then he was mistaken.

25:36.827 --> 25:40.160
I told you you should've killed him
when you had the chance.

25:44.043 --> 25:45.999
We'll never make it in there.

25:46.545 --> 25:48.501
There's always a way, Merlin.

26:00.059 --> 26:01.890
